  "summary": "Focused c3 rows4/5/6 QKV/scratch diagnostic after input RMSNorm was eliminated. Forcing full-attention QKV prep to the per-row scratch path engages per_row_qkv_scratch_fallback but leaves generated-token prefixes unchanged at [11,60,117] and keeps the same first full-attention hidden mismatch as native full: decode step 0, layer7, attn_input_pre_qkv, row0. Forcing independent per-row full-attention layer scratch is also not a fix and worsens row prefixes to [11,11,40]; its short hidden trace produced non-finite values before JSON serialization. Rowchunk2 remains the green control [137,137,137]. Therefore QKV prep/scratch replay alone is eliminated; next work should target the upstream hidden/row-group interaction before or at the full-attention pre-QKV boundary, or a more direct native-vs-rowchunk differential of layer7 inputs.",
